  "body": "When building from source, the build system makes a deep clone of LLVM and other dependencies, downloading several hundred megabytes, which takes a significant time over a slow connection. A shallow clone (done with `git submodule update --depth 1`, see http://stackoverflow.com/a/17692710/2754323 ) would only download the latest revision of the dependencies, since the rest of the commit history is not needed, and save bandwidth and space at no (as far as I know) cost.\n",
